<div class="modal fade" id="unitLoadsHelp" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title">Unit Loads Help</h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>Unit Loads (UL) represent internal SSCC identifiers linked to receipts.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>SSCC</strong>: internal identifier generated by the system. External SSCC is optional.</li>
                    <li><strong>Status</strong>: Created indicates ready to print; Printed indicates a label was generated.</li>
                    <li><strong>Receipt</strong>: UL must be linked to an existing receipt.</li>
                    <li><strong>Re-label</strong>: generates a new internal SSCC and stores the old/new values in history.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Use the <strong>New Unit Load</strong> action to create a UL and print its label. On the details screen you can re-label the UL and review its history.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
